<item>
            <title>[HBASE-2649] Make use of storefile &apos;order&apos; making certain decisions during merge sort</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2649</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When we merge sort results currently there is no regard for storefile order.  This issue is about exploiting store file order at certain junctures.  For example, if we have N KVs all of the same coordinates &amp;#8211; same r/f/q/type/ts &amp;#8211; then the one from the storefile that was made most recently should prevail.  Also, we might consider order when looking at deletes so our tombstones are less &lt;b&gt;tombstoney&lt;/b&gt; in that they&apos;ll only apply to values that are in storefiles older than the one that carries the delete marker (this latter sounds hard but putting it out there anyways).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12465913">HBASE-2649</key>
            <summary>Make use of storefile &apos;order&apos; making certain decisions during merge sort</summary>
